This is generally acknowledged in many historical sources, including the Brethren Encylopedia and the citation that is provided. Showalter wrote only the music for the chorus even though he was given credit for all of the music upon publication. The publishers didn't realize that the music for the verses had actually come from his nephew, one of his students at Bridgewater College.
